Osun State Governor and governorship candidate of the All Progressives Congress in the July 16 governorship poll, Adegboyega Oyetola, on Thursday, expressed optimism for a victorious outing for the ruling party in the poll. Oyetola spoke in Osogbo at the opening of a seminar organised by Gboyega Oyetola Foundation. The governor restated his commitment to good governance and lauded the management of the foundation for the initiative, saying, “I am deeply involved in the foundation. I am committed to good governance but, while working towards that, we should know that voters’ orientation is paramount. I commend the brain behind Gboyega Oyetola foundation. “I am optimistic of victory in the forthcoming poll. We have done our best since coming on board. I urge you all to collect PVC and vote for APC in the governorship poll.” Chairman of the foundation, Chief Felix Awofisayo, explained that Oyetola’s vision gave birth to the initiative. He added that the mission was to use the platform to source funds from private individuals and corporate bodies that would be used to ensure good governance, wellness of the people, availability of good education and empowerment for the youths.